# ROCm/HIP docs root-level inventory

upstream_repo: ROCm/hip
upstream_path: docs/
source_view: GitHub mobile file browser screenshots supplied by project owner
created_for: Netiv ROCN research library
scope: docs/ first-level folders and files only
status: manual staged inventory

FORMAT:
path | kind | apparent purpose

================================================================================
DOCS FIRST-LEVEL FOLDERS
================================================================================
docs/data/ | folder | Documentation data assets and generated/input data fragments.
docs/doxygen/ | folder | Doxygen documentation generation configuration/output support.
docs/doxygen-input/ | folder | Doxygen input configuration and source fragments.
docs/extension/ | folder | Sphinx/custom documentation extensions.
docs/how-to/ | folder | Practical HIP usage guides and how-to documentation.
docs/install/ | folder | HIP installation and source-build documentation.
docs/reference/ | folder | HIP API/reference documentation.
docs/sphinx/ | folder | Sphinx documentation build configuration and table-of-contents support.
docs/tools/ | folder | Documentation support tools and example-code assets.
docs/tutorial/ | folder | HIP tutorials and guided examples.
docs/understand/ | folder | Conceptual explanation of HIP architecture, programming model, compiler model, and hardware behavior.

================================================================================
DOCS ROOT FILES
================================================================================
docs/.gitignore | config | Ignore rules specific to documentation build/generated files.
docs/conf.py | build config | Sphinx documentation configuration.
docs/device_md_gen.py | script | Python helper for generating device markdown/documentation metadata.
docs/environment.yml | environment config | Conda/environment configuration for documentation tooling.
docs/faq.rst | docs page | HIP frequently asked questions.
docs/gen_clang_option_doc.sh | script | Shell helper for generating Clang option documentation.
docs/hip-7-changes.rst | docs page | HIP 7.x/API change notes.
docs/index.md | docs page | Main HIP documentation landing page.
docs/license.md | legal/docs page | Documentation/license information.
docs/what_is_hip.rst | docs page | Introductory explanation of what HIP is.

================================================================================
ROCN NOTES
================================================================================
This folder is high-value for ROCN because it tells us how AMD explains HIP's programming model before we study implementation details.

Best ROCN targets under docs/ for next deeper passes:

1. docs/understand/
   Use for ROCN vocabulary and conceptual mapping.

2. docs/how-to/
   Use for host/device runtime behavior, memory movement, kernel launch, streams, graphs, interop, and runtime compilation behavior.

3. docs/reference/
   Use for API surface mapping after we understand the model.

4. docs/tutorial/
   Use for simple example-driven Netiv translations later.

Do not vendor docs content into NetivLang yet. Treat this as an upstream map for original ROCN design work.
